parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission range sensor can cause the vehicle to slip out of gear, lose power, and jerk while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle slips out of gear
loses power
jerks while driving
the check engine light illuminates
the vehicle will not accelerate
the transmission engages into neutral without warning
the vehicle drags or will not accelerate over 10 mph
the vehicle makes a clunking or banging noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip out of gear, and jerk while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
slips out of gear
jerks while driving
the transmission engages into neutral without warning
the vehicle drags or will not accelerate over 10 mph
the vehicle makes a clunking or banging noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter lock solenoid can cause the vehicle to be stuck in park, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle is stuck in park
the shifter lock solenoid fails to engage
the vehicle will not shift out of park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, damage to the vehicle's interior, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Headlights stay on
smoke or fire from the instrument panel
burning smell
transmission range sensor failure
daytime running lights malfunction
and battery drain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission range sensor can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Transmission slipping gears
stuck in 3rd gear
and failure to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Headlamp and Daytime Running Light Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the headlamps and daytime running lights can cause reduced visibility, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Headlights stay on
daytime running lights malfunction
and failure to turn off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Bag Light Illumination and Passenger Seat Occupancy Detection Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger seat occupancy detection system can lead to the air bag light illumination, which may cause the air bags to malfunction in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The air bag light on the dashboard remains illuminated
indicating that the air bag is not engaged
even when a passenger is seated in the front seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bags to deploy in the event of an accident can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The air bags fail to deploy during an accident
even when the vehicle is severely damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadvertent deployment of the air bags can cause injuries and distractions while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The air bags deploy without warning
even when there is no accident or collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the air bag system can cause the air bags to fail to deploy or deploy inadvertently, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The air bag system malfunctions
causing the air bag light to illuminate
or the air bags to deploy without warning.
